[normal]Altogether, RWE is spending around €9 million on the 
[normal]Niederaussem 
[normal]development project. The German federal government contributed about €4 million to the cost of the pilot plant
[normal]. 
[normal]The North Carolina project is being su
[normal]pported in part by a $2 million grant from the US Department of Energy.  
[normal]The ambition of the current and previous Government to make the UK a global export champion for CCS technologies is bold
[normal]. It
[normal] has not happ
[normal]ened yet and
[normal] might be more credible if 
[normal]narrowly focused on specific parts of the value chain with serious potential for comparative advantage
[normal]. It might be more credible for the UK to focus on partnership rather than leadership
[normal] within international teams.
[normal] 
[normal]We recognise internationalism is a part of the UK approach, but 
[normal] 
[normal]premised on an assumption collaboration will be delivered by companies that have succeeded in the UK first, based around the pilot projects that have been two years away from starting for muc
[normal]h of the last decade.  
[normal]We do not 
[normal]then 
[normal]believe the UK can or will be global leaders in 
[normal]all
[normal] CCS 
[normal]technologies and suspect 
[normal]the desire to ‘build it here’, evident since the 
[normal]abort
[normal]ed BP Peterhead project
[normal] (2007)
